| HistoryText             = The Prime Sentinels were created when [[Bastion (Earth-616)|Bastion]] initiated the [[Operation: Zero Tolerance]] program.{{Citation}} These [[Sentinels]] were actually [[Homo sapiens|humans]] who had been fitted with cybernetic nanotech implants, which, upon activation, transformed the humans into armored beings with powerful weapons systems.{{Citation}} These altered humans set up as sleeper agents, unaware of their natures until a signal from the Operation: Zero Tolerance base activated their programming.{{Citation}} These Sentinels were used by Bastion to capture [[Charles Xavier (Earth-616)|Professor X]] for his own purposes, as well as attack various mutants associated with the X-Men across the country.{{Citation}} Bastion and his Prime Sentinels were eventually defeated by the [[X-Men (Earth-616)|X-Men]] with help from the government agency, [[Strategic Homeland Intervention, Enforcement and Logistics Division (Earth-616)|S.H.I.E.L.D.]], who shut down Operation: Zero Tolerance.{{Citation}}

The Omega Prime Sentinel class was a scrapped prototype design initially conceived by the director of the Prime Sentinel Network, Bastion, and intended to spearhead the Zero Tolerance initiative, with the most recent addition to his ranks, [[Karima Shapandar (Earth-616)|Karima Shapandar]], to be among the first of many whom he would soon create in order to lead his Bio-Sentinel forces.{{Citation}} Bastion revitalized it through the [[Techno-Organic Virus|Transmode / Apocalypse Virus]] while creating his [[Human Council (Earth-616)|Human High Council]].{{Citation}} Similar to the standard Prime Sentinel precursors, Omega Primes were Sentinels who were forcibly modified through an infection of nanotechnology injected into them by the mutant hunting Synthenoid who created them.{{Citation}} But these were apparently prototypes, as their designs were clunkier than other Prime Sentinels.{{Citation}} The only difference being their ability to adapt and evolve new and deadly mechanical apparatuses through their biomechanical microtech, which made up their cybernetic anatomy.{{Citation}}

In a unique twist, Bastion would eventually revive the Omega Sentinel program after being revived through his use of a Spawn of the Technarchy known as [[Magus (Technarch) (Earth-616)|Magus]].{{Citation}} As the Nimrod programming began to act irregularly with the Celestial Technology within his system, Bastion began to revert into his Nimrod persona and, in the act of which, transformed two of his Councilmen into advanced Prime Sentinels reminiscent to Nimrod himself.{{Citation}}

